53
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:39,628
So why don't you save us both a lot of time

54
00:04:39,777 --> 00:04:43,116
and tell me how you cheated.

55
00:04:58,035 --> 00:05:04,017
I'm done sir.

56
00:05:04,052 --> 00:05:07,217
Now listen.

57
00:05:09,394 --> 00:05:11,748
Hello!

58
00:05:14,149 --> 00:05:16,048
He's is unconscious,
chutiya. What good is that?

59
00:05:16,349 --> 00:05:18,726
How many times have I told
you, you should once...

60
00:05:19,852 --> 00:05:21,051
I'm sorry sir.

61
00:05:21,052 --> 00:05:21,965
(Speaks Hindi)

62
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Now we'll have Amnesty International here

63
00:05:24,035 --> 00:05:27,000
peeing in their pants about human rights.

64
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:27,965
Sir I was thinking...

65
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Get him down, tidy him up please.
For God's sake!

66
00:05:32,035 --> 00:05:37,965
Sir, what if he did know whe answers?

67
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,000
Professors, doctors, lawyers,
general knowledge-wallas

68
00:05:41,035 --> 00:05:43,000
never get beyond 60000 rupees.

69
00:05:43,035 --> 00:05:44,965
He's on 10 million.

70
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:51,000
What can a slumdog possibly know?

71
00:05:51,035 --> 00:05:58,035
The answers.

72
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:04,500
I knew the answers.

73
00:06:04,535 --> 00:06:09,767
Slumdog Millionaire.

74
00:06:09,802 --> 00:06:13,451
Jamal, catch it!

75
00:06:15,220 --> 00:06:17,591
Jamal, it's yours!

76
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,146
How did you manage to drop
a sitter like that, damn it?

77
00:06:27,181 --> 00:06:29,757
Private ka-land!

78
00:06:32,035 --> 00:06:33,769
Catch him!

79
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,527
The dogs are coming! Run!

80
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,559
If the planes won't kill you, we will!

81
00:06:48,035 --> 00:06:50,224
Hey brother!

82
00:08:19,035 --> 00:08:21,330
Sorry!

83
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,577
I'm very sorry.

84
00:08:36,345 --> 00:08:38,059
Oh shit, it's Mum.

85
00:08:38,094 --> 00:08:39,504
You want me to wallop you to death, huh?

86
00:08:41,035 --> 00:08:43,948
Brother, leave these two to me.

87
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,488
Come on.

88
00:08:50,368 --> 00:08:52,001
Athos.

89
00:08:57,340 --> 00:08:59,236
The Three Musketeers.

90
00:08:59,237 --> 00:09:03,040
Repeat it!
"You have sent for me, Sir?" said Athos.

91
00:09:05,361 --> 00:09:08,509
Ah, here come our very own musketeers.

92
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,115
Thank you for gracing us all
with your presence.

93
00:09:13,035 --> 00:09:14,170
Porthos!

94
00:09:14,205 --> 00:09:15,835
Well, open it, Salim.

95
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,331
Stop doing that and open the book, Jamal.

96
00:09:22,435 --> 00:09:23,249
Athos?

97
00:09:42,479 --> 00:09:45,226
So... Mr. Malik

98
00:09:46,610 --> 00:09:48,548
the man who knows all the answers.

99
00:09:51,036 --> 00:09:51,966
Talk.

100
00:09:53,637 --> 00:09:55,150
(Speaks Hindi) Talk!

101
00:10:00,274 --> 00:10:04,231
So Jamal, are you ready for the
first question, for 1000 rupees?

102
00:10:05,035 --> 00:10:06,965
Yes.

103
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Not bad money to sit on a chair

104
00:10:08,035 --> 00:10:09,965
and answer a question.

105
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Better than making tea, no?

106
00:10:13,035 --> 00:10:14,965
No. Yes. No.

107
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:19,500
No? Yes? No? Is that your final answer?

108
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:24,000
So remember. You have three lifelines.

109
00:10:24,035 --> 00:10:28,000
Ask the audience, fifty-fifty

110
00:10:28,035 --> 00:10:29,965
and call a friend.

111
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:33,859
So the first question, for 1000 rupees,
here we go.

112
00:10:34,035 --> 00:10:40,857
Who was the star in the 1973
hit-film "Zanjeer"?

113
00:10:51,035 --> 00:10:52,692
I'm in trouble, here...

114
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:58,999
Here... Money. Take the money...

115
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Get out of there, Jamal.
Prakash wants a big one.

116
00:11:07,035 --> 00:11:09,999
Not finished.

117
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,132
Stop your time-pass boys. This is urgent...

118
00:11:12,133 --> 00:11:14,326
It's a shy one...

119
00:11:14,327 --> 00:11:17,119
and since when there is
a time limit on a crap?

120
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:19,965
This is borderline kid. Get a move on...

121
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:24,000
Since there was a customer waiting,
that's when Jamal!

122
00:11:24,035 --> 00:11:27,000
Give me the money back!
Give! I'll go elsewhere.

123
00:11:27,035 --> 00:11:29,965
Bloody idiot.

124
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:34,000
You just lost me a bloody customer.

125
00:11:34,035 --> 00:11:36,965
Amitabh's helicopter!

126
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,235
That's Amitabh's helicopter!

127
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:39,705
Amitabh!

128
00:11:41,922 --> 00:11:44,420
Amitabh Bachchan!

129
00:12:00,236 --> 00:12:01,280
Salim, open it!

130
00:12:42,509 --> 00:12:44,654
Amitabh Bachchan!

131
00:13:01,140 --> 00:13:02,877
My Amitabh sir!

132
00:13:03,629 --> 00:13:05,237
Move, move! Out of the way!

133
00:13:05,272 --> 00:13:07,783
Please wait, I am coming for you!

134
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:12,846
Amitabh sir, please give me your autograph

135
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:40,940
You've got it now have you?
Amitabh's autograph?

136
00:14:17,073 --> 00:14:19,661
That was my autograph!

137
00:14:19,696 --> 00:14:21,710
Amitabh gave it to me!

138
00:14:21,811 --> 00:14:23,519
I'll never get another!

139
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:27,034
He offered a good price, so I sold it.

140
00:14:27,102 --> 00:14:29,330
But it was mine...

141
00:14:30,552 --> 00:14:33,965
A, Amitabh Bachchan.

142
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,986
Guess what, you're right.
You just won 1,000 rupees.

143
00:14:41,035 --> 00:14:42,481
You don't have to be a genius.

144
00:14:42,593 --> 00:14:45,075
I knew it was Amitabh Bachchan.

145
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:49,503
Like I said, you do not have to be a genius.

146
00:14:53,035 --> 00:14:54,906
He's the most famous man in India.

147
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:01,067
A picture of three lions, as seen
on the national emblem of India.

148
00:15:02,035 --> 00:15:04,438
What is written underneath?

149
00:15:05,052 --> 00:15:08,043
A: The truth alone triumphs

150
00:15:08,078 --> 00:15:11,262
B: Lies alone triumph

151
00:15:11,552 --> 00:15:14,122
C: Fashion alone triumphs

152
00:15:14,928 --> 00:15:18,531
D: Money alone triumphs

153
00:15:23,664 --> 00:15:25,465
What do you think, Jamal?

154
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:29,910
The most famous phrase of our country.

155
00:15:30,035 --> 00:15:32,450
Do you like to call a friend?

156
00:15:32,485 --> 00:15:34,965
Ask the audience.

157
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,965
Who'd put him out of his
misery, ladies and gentlemen?

158
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:41,000
My five-year old daughter
can answer that question,

159
00:15:41,035 --> 00:15:42,387
but you couldn't.

160
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,221
That's strange for a millionaire genius.

161
00:15:46,035 --> 00:15:47,486
What happened?

162
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Your accomplice sneaked out for a piss?

163
00:15:51,035 --> 00:15:53,965
The inspector is asking something.

164
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:57,132
How much is panipuri at
Dharisha store on Chowpatty?

165
00:15:57,930 --> 00:15:59,339
What?

166
00:15:59,374 --> 00:16:02,830
Panipuri. One plate. How much?

167
00:16:03,035 --> 00:16:05,034
- 10 rupees.
- Wrong.

168
00:16:05,035 --> 00:16:06,021
15 since Diwali.

169
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,634
Who stole Constable Varmy's bicycle

170
00:16:10,635 --> 00:16:13,347
outside Santa Cruz station last Thursday?

171
00:16:15,035 --> 00:16:16,406
You know who that was?

172
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,000
Everyone in Juhu knows that.

173
00:16:19,035 --> 00:16:21,855
Even five year olds.

174
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,953
Congratulations, Jamal.
You just won 4,000 rupees.

175
00:16:34,035 --> 00:16:36,285
A 16 thousand rupees.

176
00:16:38,552 --> 00:16:41,978
Religion. Interesting.

177
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:45,716
In depictions of God Rama he is

178
00:16:45,717 --> 00:16:49,369
famously holding what in his right hand?

179
00:17:34,736 --> 00:17:38,012
Run!

180
00:17:42,789 --> 00:17:44,557
Salim, Jamal! Run!

181
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,086
They're Muslims, get them!

182
00:18:46,284 --> 00:18:48,711
Get a move on! Come with us!

183
00:18:59,215 --> 00:19:00,850
Hey, get lost!

184
00:19:00,851 --> 00:19:04,322
Are you deaf? I said piss off!

185
00:19:09,035 --> 00:19:10,866
Come with us.

186
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:27,540
I wake up every morning wishing I did
not know the answer to that question.

187
00:19:31,035 --> 00:19:35,000
If it wasn't for Rama and Allah...

188
00:19:35,035 --> 00:19:38,524
I would still have a mother.

189
00:19:47,865 --> 00:19:49,649
A bow and arrow.

190
00:19:50,103 --> 00:19:51,326
Final answer?

191
00:19:53,863 --> 00:19:55,055
Final answer.

192
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,168
Computer, (speaks Hindi) D (speaks Hindi)?

193
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,250
You just won 16000 rupees.

194
00:20:10,138 --> 00:20:12,357
Well done, my friend.

195
00:20:14,647 --> 00:20:17,123
Time for commercial break.
Don't go away now.

196
00:20:19,035 --> 00:20:20,965
You got lucky, huh?

197
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:23,261
If I were you I'd take the money and run.

198
00:20:24,035 --> 00:20:26,065
You're not going to the next one.

199
00:21:00,035 --> 00:21:01,499
Piss off!

200
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:03,690
She'll have the security guard on us!

201
00:21:03,691 --> 00:21:05,099
Let her in.

202
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,462
She could be the third musketeer.

203
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:14,891
I'm the elder in this family now,
and I say, she's not coming in, okay?

204
00:21:16,035 --> 00:21:16,999
In any case...

205
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:21,039
We don't even know the name
of the third bloody musketeer.

206
00:21:41,192 --> 00:21:42,538
Salim?

207
00:21:59,035 --> 00:22:00,707
Come over here.

208
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,911
Where's your mother?

209
00:22:18,035 --> 00:22:19,930
Your father?

210
00:22:23,656 --> 00:22:25,150
I'm Jamal.

211
00:22:25,185 --> 00:22:27,480
This is my brother Salim.

212
00:22:29,035 --> 00:22:30,892
I'm Latika.

213
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,909
You can sleep here if you want.

214
00:22:41,035 --> 00:22:42,987
Thank you Jamal.

215
00:22:58,950 --> 00:23:01,144
Welcome back to "Who
Wants To Be A Milionaire?"

216
00:23:01,179 --> 00:23:05,000
Our contestant, Jamal Malik,
call-center assistant from Mumbay,

217
00:23:05,035 --> 00:23:06,577
is on 16 thousand rupees,

218
00:23:07,006 --> 00:23:10,322
and has already used only one
lifeline, ask the audience.

219
00:23:12,035 --> 00:23:15,638
So my friend, you're into serious money.

220
00:23:17,035 --> 00:23:18,794
Shall we play?

221
00:23:19,035 --> 00:23:20,515
Yes.

222
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:31,000
The song "Darshan Do Ghanshyam" was
written by which famous Indian poet?

223
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:33,517
A: Surdas

224
00:23:33,552 --> 00:23:35,776
B: Tulsidas

225
00:23:35,811 --> 00:23:37,608
C: Mira Bai

226
00:23:38,038 --> 00:23:40,312
D: Kabir

227
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:43,948
It's hot, huh?

228
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:38,252
The way he's taking care of
us, he must be a good man.

229
00:25:38,253 --> 00:25:39,999
Must be a bloody saint

230
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:42,275
We're not allowed to talk to the others.

231
00:25:42,276 --> 00:25:43,999
Why?

232
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:48,417
If we get seconds, then
he really must be a saint.

233
00:26:08,035 --> 00:26:10,902
Very good, Arvind. Very good.

234
00:26:24,038 --> 00:26:26,634
Laughing at me. I'll kill you.

235
00:26:26,635 --> 00:26:29,051
Hey, get off her.

236
00:26:29,452 --> 00:26:31,460
Don't touch me!

237
00:26:31,461 --> 00:26:33,030
You fat bastard!

238
00:26:35,326 --> 00:26:36,967
You big tree!

239
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:39,430
Punnoose, I think you've found your dog.

240
00:26:53,035 --> 00:26:56,556
Okay, time to go. Get to work.

241
00:27:04,759 --> 00:27:06,607
Think you're here for a picnic?

242
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:10,868
What do you think this is, a holiday?

243
00:27:13,035 --> 00:27:15,791
And what are you laughing at?

244
00:27:19,635 --> 00:27:21,165
Give me that.

245
00:27:26,091 --> 00:27:26,803
Shut up!

246
00:27:27,529 --> 00:27:28,263
Brother Salim.

247
00:27:28,791 --> 00:27:30,676
What's up little brother, you got a problem?

248
00:27:30,677 --> 00:27:32,675
Hey take her. She's yours today.

249
00:27:32,676 --> 00:27:34,063
I don't want her.

250
00:27:34,064 --> 00:27:37,207
Take her. It's for your own
good. Babies earn double.

251
00:27:37,208 --> 00:27:39,535
She said she doesn't want her.

252
00:27:39,536 --> 00:27:40,512
Shut it Jamal!

253
00:27:41,849 --> 00:27:44,339
Take her now or i'll drop her.

254
00:27:48,935 --> 00:27:52,310
Keep her crying, and you'll earn triple.

255
00:27:54,060 --> 00:27:56,638
Come on! Get to work!

256
00:28:22,035 --> 00:28:25,783
We'll use the hottest ones.

257
00:29:19,645 --> 00:29:24,657
Chillies on his willy!

258
00:29:30,932 --> 00:29:32,532
I'll get you back!

259
00:29:34,276 --> 00:29:36,150
Go back to sleep all of you!

260
00:30:01,035 --> 00:30:04,419
Very good. I am happy.

261
00:30:05,217 --> 00:30:08,541
He's ready. - I'm ready as well.

262
00:30:24,035 --> 00:30:25,846
Come on, move the lamp.

263
00:31:10,035 --> 00:31:11,815
Okay.

264
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:19,714
Bring Jamal over.

265
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:40,517
Listen, kid. It's decision time.

266
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:45,193
You want the life of a slumdog
